 Torres至少有2个儿子。她于1128年在意大利西西利亞梅西那被列为founded a hospital named after s. giovanni 。她去世在意大利西西利亞梅西那。"},"hr":{"about 1080–":"oko 1080.–preminula","1064–1127":"1064–1127","1110–1182":"1110–1182","–Male":"preminuo","1080–Female":"1080–preminula","1080":"1080","after 1127":"nakon 1127.","1127":"1127","about 1080":"oko 1080.","1110":"1110","1064":"1064","about 1110":"oko 1110.","1182":"1182","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Italija","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Italija","Messina, Sicily, Italy":"Messina, Sicilia, Italija"},"cs":{"about 1080–":"okolo 1080–Zesnulá","1064–1127":"1064–1127","1110–1182":"1110–1182","–Male":"Zesnulý","1080–Female":"1080–Zesnulá","1080":"1080","after 1127":"po 1127","1127":"1127","about 1080":"okolo 1080","1110":"1110","1064":"1064","about 1110":"okolo 1110","1182":"1182","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Itálie","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Itálie","Messina, Sicily, Italy":"Messina, Sicilia, Itálie"},"da":{"about 1080–":"omkring 1080–Afdød","1064–1127":"1064–1127","1110–1182":"1110–1182","–Male":"Afdød","1080–Female":"1080–Afdød","1080":"1080","after 1127":"efter 1127","1127":"1127","about 1080":"omkring 1080","1110":"1110","1064":"1064","about 1110":"omkring 1110","1182":"1182","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Italien","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Italien","Messina, Sicily, Italy":"Messina, Sicilia, Italien"},"nl":{"about 1080–":"circa 1080–Overleden","1064–1127":"1064–1127","1110–1182":"1110–1182","–Male":"Overleden","1080–Female":"1080–Overleden","1080":"1080","after 1127":"na 1127","1127":"1127","about 1080":"circa 1080","1110":"1110","1064":"1064","about 1110":"circa 1110","1182":"1182","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Italië","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Italië","Messina, Sicily, Italy":"Messina, Sicilia, Italië"},"en":{"about 1080–":"about 1080–Deceased","1064–1127":"1064–1127","1110–1182":"1110–1182","–Male":"Deceased","1080–Female":"1080–Deceased","1080":"1080","after 1127":"after 1127","1127":"1127","about 1080":"about 1080","1110":"1110","1064":"1064","about 1110":"about 1110","1182":"1182","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardinia, Italy","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy","Messina, Sicily, Italy":"Messina, Sicily, Italy","nameMeanings":[{"name":"di","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 狄, a term referring to the tribes in ancient northern China: (i) from Di (狄), the name of an ancient state (thought to have been located in Hebei or Shandong province), which was granted to Xiao Bo or Kao Bo by King Cheng of Zhou (reigned 1042–1021  BC ). (ii) adopted as a surname by the Ku Di (庫狄) family during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) traced back to other minority ethnic groups in ancient northwestern China.","Mandarin form of the Chinese surname 邸, meaning ‘official residence’ in Chinese: (i) from placename Di (邸), the name of a county (unidentified location). (ii) said to be borne by some descendants of Kujula Kadphises (called 丘就郤 or 邸就郤 in Chinese, 30–<i>c.</i> 80  AD ), founder of the Kushan Empire (one branch of the Yuezhi people originating from western China) located in Central Asia during the Eastern Han dynasty (25–220  AD )."],"variants":[{"name":"Chi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Dong, Yun, Cheng, Jae, Yong, Cheng Chung, Chi, Chun, Duk, Fang, Feng.  Korean Chung, Chong, Jae Hong, Moon, Myong, Pong, Shen, Yoo, Byung, Chang, Chol, Chong Hun.  Southeast Asian Phi, Hung, Ly, Tu, Denh, Do Van, Duong, Hao, Kieu, Mui, Nga, Phat.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 池, meaning ‘moat’ in ancient Chinese: (i) acquired as a surname by people who lived beside a moat. (ii) from Chi (池), said to be the name of an ancient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]},{"name":"Marcusa","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The original Latin form of   Mark  , of unknown derivation; it may possibly be connected with <i>Mars</i>, the name of the Roman god of war, or the adjective <i>mas</i> ‘male, virile’ (genitive <i>maris</i>). This was one of the very small number of Roman given names of the classical period. There were only about a dozen of these in general use, with perhaps another dozen confined to particular families. <i>Marcus</i> has been in use in the English-speaking world since the 16th century if not earlier; in the 20th century it enjoyed a considerable increase in popularity. As an African-American name it is sometimes bestowed in honour of the Black Consciousness leader  Marcus Garvey  (  1887–1940 )."],"variants":[]},{"name":"'Maria'","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A name derived from Mapia, one of the Greek forms of Miriam. Maria is found as a male name as well as a female name. Viscount Montague, of Cowdray, Sussex, who succeeded to the title as second viscount, was christened Anthony Maria Browne. In Camden's Remains (p. 44), referred to in Delicie Literarise, occurs Thomas Maria Wingfield; and there was also a Sir Edward Maria Wingfield. The name appears to have been adopted in the latter family from Mary, daughter of Henry VIII. Compare Notes and Queries 5th S. ii. 73, 316, 478. Marie is frequently found as a male name in France and in other parts of the Continent."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Marcusa 'Maria' di Arrubu was born about 1080, in Arborea, Sardinia, Italy. She had at least 2 sons with Constantine I de Torres, Judge of Torres. In 1128, her occupation is listed as founded a hospital named after s. giovanni  in Messina, Sicily, Italy. She died in Messina, Sicily, Italy."},"et":{"about 1080–":"umbes 1080–Surnud","1064–1127":"1064–1127","1110–1182":"1110–1182","–Male":"Surnud","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1080":"1080","after 1127":"pärast 1127","1127":"1127","about 1080":"umbes 1080","1110":"1110","1064":"1064","about 1110":"umbes 1110","1182":"1182","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Itaalia","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Itaalia","Messina, Sicily, Italy":"Messina, Sicilia, Itaalia"},"fi":{"about 1080–":"noin 1080–Kuollut","1064–1127":"1064–1127","1110–1182":"1110–1182","–Male":"Kuollut","1080–Female":"1080–Kuollut","1080":"1080","after 1127":"1127 jälkeen","1127":"1127","about 1080":"noin 1080","1110":"1110","1064":"1064","about 1110":"noin 1110","1182":"1182","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Italia","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Italia","Messina, Sicily, Italy":"Messina, Sicilia, Italia"},"fr":{"about 1080–":"environ 1080–Décédée","1064–1127":"1064–1127","1110–1182":"1110–1182","–Male":"Décédé","1080–Female":"1080–Décédée","1080":"1080","after 1127":"après 1127","1127":"1127","about 1080":"environ 1080","1110":"1110","1064":"1064","about 1110":"environ 1110","1182":"1182","Arborea, Sardinia, Italy":"Arborea, Sardegna, Italie","Logudoro, Sardinia, Italy":"Logudoro, Sardegna, Italie","Messina, Sicily, Italy":"Messina, Sicile, Italie","lifeSummary":"Marcusa 'Maria' di Arrubu est née environ 1080, à Arborea, Sardegna, Italie. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils avec Constantine I de Torres, Judge of Torres. En 1128, la profession de sa indiquée est f